\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/peel/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Peel}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/devein/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 devein}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butterfly/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 butterfly}} the shrimp, leaving the tails on. Place the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/shrimp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 shrimp}} in a mixing bowl and toss gently with the olive oil, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/wine/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 wine}}, 2 teaspoons salt, and 1 teaspoon pepper. Allow to sit at room temperature while you make the butter and garlic mixture.\
\
In a small bowl, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mash/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mash}} the softened butter with the garlic, shallots, parsley, rosemary, red pepper flakes, lemon zest, lemon juice, egg yolk, panko, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper until combined.\
\
Starting from the outer edge of a 14-inch oval gratin dish, arrange the shrimp in a single layer cut side down with the tails curling up and towards the center of the dish. Pour the remaining {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/marinade/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 marinade}} over the shrimp. Spread the butter mixture evenly over the shrimp. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until hot and bubbly. If you like the top browned, place under a broiler for 1 minute. Serve with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon}} wedges.\
